The integrity code had been inserted into the party charter as Mr Kenyatta sought to project himself as the leader to bring a fresh approach to politics devoid of old hang-ups, ethnic loyalties and acceptance of corruption as a norm.
In much the same way, Mr Kenyatta had unsuccessfully sought to reshape the Kanu Party after controversially being handpicked by outgoing President Daniel arap Moi to carry the flag in 2002, he now hoped to market TNA as the cleaner, fresher successor to President Mwai Kibaki’s governing coalition.



