Loot the national coffers
Unfortunately, the integrity code has thus far been observed only in the breach. There is little to show that the changes proposed under BBI will offer anything more than lip service to the most urgent need to eradicate the cancer from our midst.
President Kenyatta has had more than enough opportunity under existing laws to strike mortal blows against corruption, but has looked on helplessly even as his own relatives, close friends and political associates loot the national coffers in a manner that rivals the worst excesses of the Moi kleptocracy.
One big achievement of BBI has been to drag Mr Odinga into the murk, and silence what was previously one of the most powerful voices against institutionalised graft and general misrule. The by-election to fill the vacant seat of Nairobi Governor presents the ‘cityzens’ a grand opportunity to assess both the Uhu-Raila and Ruto groupings.
 The measure will be on which of them fronts an upright, competent, incorruptible candidate; and which the usual crooked and sleazy city politico.
*** *** ***
Times are hard. So I deviated from my normal morning hike through the bundu to up and down by the front door of the Kenya Medical Supplies Authority in the dust and grime of Nairobi’s Industrial Area. No luck so far.



